{"TopicId":154572,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Drag racing idea","CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-06T07:06:55Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-23T03:35:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s/view?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EBETA Drag Parts\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is obviously a WIP, still no wheels and apparently I need an older version of unity for animations.\u00A0 You will need Azimech\u0027s original parts as well for any of these to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-23T19:19:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222931264\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154572\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485142502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002211888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SasquatchM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, SasquatchM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s/view?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EBETA Drag Parts\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is obviously a WIP, still no wheels and apparently I need an older version of unity for animations.\u00A0 You will need Azimech\u0027s original parts as well for any of these to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love it ! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_cool.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022\u003E Thanks !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/AyHxfnO71ic?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-28T01:49:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223LqCQYs.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/3LqCQYs.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022G2ozm24.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/G2ozm24.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone have any ideas?\u00A0 Steering, suspension and movement are all working fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-28T01:49:39Z\u0022 title=\u002201/28/2017 01:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 28, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by SasquatchM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-28T02:06:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuccess!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/VMcWdIy.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022VMcWdIy.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheel Colliders have to line up with actual wheel meshes now it seems\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-28T15:18:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222936846\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154572\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485569207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002211888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SasquatchM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, SasquatchM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheel Colliders have to line up with actual wheel meshes now it seems\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi what actually causes\u00A0 that is that whatever the suspension transform is called is not in the correct position, as long as it is aligned with the wheel collider there are no issues but if for some reason the collider and the transform are separated, the game code pulls\u00A0 everything back into line as your first pic. For ref I\u0027ve found the best placement for the WC\u0027s if using stock is on the extreme outer edge of the wheel mesh, although if you\u0027ve set up for the KSP wheels API always center the collider to the wheel mesh, this gives some advanced collider typ detection options which transform wheels completely\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-28T17:28:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood to know. I may go and move the collider a bit, but i thin kthe wheel itself is wide enough where the collider placement seems to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/CkVsQH0uQiA?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-29T01:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts are updated to include front and rear wheels - Azimech\u0027s originals are still required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheelie bar and cfg tweaks are all that are left - at least that I can think of\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/lKa-VmGRv3w?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the wobbles may be caused by how the wheels utilize the torque resource.\u00A0 The wheels top speed is set to 500 some m/s, but they run out of torque before they get near that speed.\u00A0 Then, like how jet engines flame out at different times when intakeAir is low, one wheel gets slightly more torque than the other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SasquatchM","CreatedById":11888,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-29T19:19:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdated models and scaling, updated cfgs, added wheelie bars\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022DdlmP0u.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DdlmP0u.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll that is left is balancing - power curves, resources and modelling a fuel tank.\u00A0 The tank apparently is usually located in the nose of dragsters, so I am considering making cowling and cockpit pieces that would fit together.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PA180020s-vi.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://images41.fotki.com/v305/photos/1/174078/4358662/PA180020s-vi.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E@Azimech \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E were you planning on balancing that stuff?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAll the pre-existing links should have the new parts.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThis will break craft as well.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?id=0B_hA1ReUylawOGJ4czhFdlpBT2s\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-29T19:29:29Z\u0022 title=\u002201/29/2017 07:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 29, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by SasquatchM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}